title: For Sale/Trade:  2006 Kawasaki Vulcan 900 Bobber For Sale / Trade
postcontent:
Looking to get this sold, need to get it out of the garage to make room for my new bike! Reasonable offers accepted. Thank you.  I'd consider trades for firearms + cash, but looking to get at least $2000 cash to buy a few modifications for my new bike.  I'd consider a 4x4 truck in trade as well.

**Copy over from craigslist**
Hello, thanks for checking out my listing. I really hate to see it go, but I've put a deposit down on another bike for sale through a friend of the family, so it's time for me to move on to the next! For sale is my 2006 Kawasaki Vulcan 900 bobber with LOTS of upgrades and modifications.

The bike is in excellent condition. It is fuel injected so no messing with carbs, which I prefer. Maintenance is much easier. It runs like a top, 0 issues mechanically and it is very clean cosmetically. Paint is perfect, completed by a local builder recently. It is ready to get on and ride. As of this posting, it has 28,2xx miles. I ride pretty frequently so it will go up over time. It is a 5 speed manual with heel shifter. This IS a soft tail, it has a full rear suspension so the ride is very comfortable.

The title is clean, clear and in hand ready to transfer.

Over the last 2 years, the bike was basically pulled apart by a local builder and had a lot of work done. I'll try to list everything, but I'm sure I'll miss something. Maintenance is up to date, it needs nothing until Spring, 2016, which will just be an oil change, check tire pressure, etc. Normal maintenance. 

The bike has never been down or dropped, these were modifications I made to suit my taste. I'm a big bobber-style fan so that's the direction I went.

New items include;

Tires (front and back, spring, 2015). It's a 230 rear, largest you can fit to the Vulcan 900.
20" front wheel was added spring, 2015
Oil change, spring, 2015
La Rosa sea with ghost black flames in fall, 2014
Bobber modifications completed in fall, 2014
-Any needed maintenance was completed during this time while the bike was mostly apart
Custom front fender, fall, 2014
Custom battery tray, fall, 2014
Custom tail light with integrated turn signals, fall, 2014
Paint was completed (matte black) in fall, 2014 (while bike was apart)
Freedom Performance slash cut exhaust, spring, 2014
Battery tender quick detach cable included, already installed.

The bike sounds mean with the slash-cut exhaust, it's a very throaty growl. It's also surprisingly sporty for what was a cruiser bike. I rode sport bikes the prior 10 or so years (moved on to this when my dad bought his first bike so we could ride together). This bike, while not as quick as a super sport, has definitely kept my interest since purchase.

If you have any questions or concerns, please let me know. I work 9am - 6pm M-F and I'm on the phone a lot, so if you call and I don't answer, please leave me a voicemail and I'll get back to you. Text and email are both fine as well.

I'll update this post with any additional information if there's anything else I think of.

A high def video walk around of the bike (with engine off and on so you can hear it running) is available on Youtube here;

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E2FUW-NOXCA

Test rides are welcome with cash in my hand.

Thank you for your interest!
